{
  "doc_id": "23037",
  "text": "ODULATED backscatter offers the prospect of extremely low power consumption for telemetry uplink from wireless devices [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Backscatter communication relies on an incident electromagnetic (EM) signal for the RF carrier and conveys information with controlled reflections of this signal [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] . Since backscatter devices do not need to generate their own RF carrier, they do not need to contain potentially complex and power-hungry local oscillators and transmit power amplifiers; thus enabling low-power low-cost communication links.",
